  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "In response to the report that a\nnew campaign for the liberty of\nfree speech on the streets in Spo-\nkane Is to be started in March by\nthe I. w. w., Chief of Police Sulli-\nvan says he is ready. He has Sc\ncured the city market building, in\nwhich he says 1900 prisoners can\nbe locked up at once, and directly\nacross the street from it is a rock\npile big enough to keep a large\nforce of men busy for two years.\nThe city has promised to buy the\nrock crushed here, at market prices.\nSullivan says the revenue will be\nspent for bread and water for the\nstreet speakers."
    }
